{#- Previous / next post navigation.

    DIRECTION — read this before touching it, it is easy to invert:
    `collections.posts` is sorted NEWEST-FIRST (index 0 = newest post). Eleventy's
    getPreviousCollectionItem / getNextCollectionItem walk the ARRAY, not the
    calendar: "previous" is index-1 and "next" is index+1. In a newest-first array
    that means

        getPreviousCollectionItem  ->  index-1  ->  the NEWER post
        getNextCollectionItem      ->  index+1  ->  the OLDER post

    which is the reverse of what a reader means. So, deliberately crossed:

        olderPost  = collections.posts | getNextCollectionItem      -> "Previous"
        newerPost  = collections.posts | getPreviousCollectionItem  -> "Next"

    Edges: the newest post has no newer neighbour and the oldest has no older one,
    so each link is rendered only if its target exists — never a dead button. The
    whole <nav> is skipped if neither exists (a one-post site). -#}
{%- set olderPost = collections.posts | getNextCollectionItem %}
{%- set newerPost = collections.posts | getPreviousCollectionItem %}

{#- `gh-canvas` is the theme's grid wrapper: it lays its DIRECT children into the
    `main` column, so it goes on an outer div and the <nav> is that single child —
    putting gh-canvas on the <nav> itself would grid-stack the two links. -#}
{%- if olderPost or newerPost %}
<div class="gh-canvas">
<nav class="gh-post-nav" aria-label="{{ 'Post navigation' | t }}">
	{%- if olderPost %}
	<a class="gh-post-nav-link gh-post-nav-prev" href="{{ olderPost.url }}" rel="prev">
		<span class="gh-post-nav-arrow">{% include "partials/icons/arrow-fat-left.njk" %}</span>
		<span class="gh-post-nav-text">
			<span class="gh-post-nav-label">{{ "Previous" | t }}</span>
			<span class="gh-post-nav-title">{{ olderPost.data.title }}</span>
		</span>
	</a>
	{%- endif %}

	{%- if newerPost %}
	<a class="gh-post-nav-link gh-post-nav-next" href="{{ newerPost.url }}" rel="next">
		<span class="gh-post-nav-text">
			<span class="gh-post-nav-label">{{ "Next" | t }}</span>
			<span class="gh-post-nav-title">{{ newerPost.data.title }}</span>
		</span>
		<span class="gh-post-nav-arrow">{% include "partials/icons/arrow-fat-right.njk" %}</span>
	</a>
	{%- endif %}
</nav>
</div>
{%- endif %}
